            "abstractNote": "Since the beginning of industrialization, energy consumption has increased far more rapidly than t number of people on the planet. It is known that the consumption of energy is amazingly high and t fossil based resources may not be able to provide energy for the whole world as these resources will used up in the near future. Hence, renewable energy expected to play an important role in handling t demand of the energy required along with environmental pollution prevention. The impacts of the wind energy on the environment are important to be studied before any wind ﬁ construction or a decision is made. Although many countries showing great interest towards renewab or green energy generation, negative perception of wind energy is increasingly evident that may preve the installation of the wind energy in some countries. This paper compiled latest literatures in terms thesis (MS and PhD), journal articles, conference proceedings, reports, books, and web materials abo the environmental impacts of wind energy. This paper also includes the comparative study of wi energy, problems, solutions and suggestion as a result of the implementation of wind turbine. Posit and negative impacts of wind energy have been broadly explained as well. It has been found that t source of energy will reduce environmental pollution and water consumption. However, it has no pollution, visual interference and negative impacts on wildlife.",
